window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Faking this relationship should be a piece of cake.</b></p> <p>Retta Majors is having a bad day - but that’s to be expected when your ex gets engaged to your cousin. Instead of (totally) freaking out, Retta decides to attend the wedding with her amazing, faithful, and handsome boyfriend. One problem....He doesn’t exist.<br> <br> Duncan Gilmore is living his dream. His boxing gym is open for business, and he’s focused on success. The last thing on his mind is a relationship. That is, until the beautiful baker next door makes him an offer so bizarre, he can’t refuse. One weekend of pretending to be Retta’s boyfriend should be easy.</p> <p>However, shared kisses and some flirting start to blur the lines in their fake relationship. When their performance draws to a close, will they go their separate ways, or return for an encore?</p> <p><b>This novel is a standalone.</b></p> <p><b>Content notes: A pregnant secondary character. </b></p>"; 
